<div id="review_2189086074" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2189086074" />
    <a title="Jacob Appel" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/22938523-jacob-appel"><img alt="Jacob Appel" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442656915p2/22938523.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2189086074?book_show_action=true">Nov 19, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jacob Appel" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jacob Appel" href="/user/show/22938523-jacob-appel">Jacob Appel</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780374534226" href="/book/show/17332376-mood-indigo">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2189086074" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16259617074468885115">What a brilliant, clever novel -- but not for the faint of imagination.<br/><br/>Vian&apos;s short novel teems with world play, spoonerisms, puns, backwards logic and verbal chaos, but at the same time manages to create an authentic and emotionally convincing world. The surreal magic of his story is the surreal magic of young love, captured perfectly through Colin&apos;s efforts to buy enough flowers to cure his beloved Chloe of the &quot;waterlily on her lung.&quot; The novel is unsparing in its satire, including masterful </span>
  <span id="freeText16259617074468885115" style="display:none">What a brilliant, clever novel -- but not for the faint of imagination.<br /><br />Vian's short novel teems with world play, spoonerisms, puns, backwards logic and verbal chaos, but at the same time manages to create an authentic and emotionally convincing world. The surreal magic of his story is the surreal magic of young love, captured perfectly through Colin's efforts to buy enough flowers to cure his beloved Chloe of the "waterlily on her lung." The novel is unsparing in its satire, including masterful commentaries on medicine, business, philosophy and the Catholic Church.<br /><br />I should emphasize that this novel is not for every reader. One line from the text I particularly admire may serve as a good litmus test: "Her footsteps on the stairs echoed away like a woodpecker falling asleep...." If you don't find 214 pages of prose in that vein compelling, maybe this isn't the bedtime reading for you.<br /><br />(I should also add that the Stanley Chapman translation is highly impressive, as this may be among the most difficult works ever to confront a translator.)<br /><br />For those unfamiliar with Vian and curious, this should prove a savory morsel.....</span>
  <a data-text-id="16259617074468885115" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


