<div id="review_2117591169" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2117591169" />
    <a title="Magdelanye" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5208681-magdelanye"><img alt="Magdelanye" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1315558024p2/5208681.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2117591169?book_show_action=true">Sep 14, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Magdelanye" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Magdelanye" href="/user/show/5208681-magdelanye">Magdelanye</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780966234633" href="/book/show/141822.Foam_of_the_Daze">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5208681-magdelanye?shelf=health-and-deterioration">health-and-deterioration</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5208681-magdelanye?shelf=postmodern-fiction">postmodern-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5208681-magdelanye?shelf=language-thought-reality">language-thought-reality</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5208681-magdelanye?shelf=coming-of-age-initiation">coming-of-age-initiation</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5208681-magdelanye?shelf=existential-crises">existential-crises</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5208681-magdelanye?shelf=alternate-reality">alternate-reality</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5208681-magdelanye?shelf=reorganizing-the-world">reorganizing-the-world</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5208681-magdelanye?shelf=social-commentary">social-commentary</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2117591169" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8408546090085746879">Quietly, gently, with dignity and respect, Boris Vian leads the astonished reader into an incongruent world, a surrealists dream where time and space have taken on more fluid dimensions. Manifestations, of painting and literature and poetry and stubborn dreams, stalk a Paris where the resistance to the Vichy regime is still going on. <br/><br/>A la Breton, BV shines a brilliant light on the most revered of our illusions: love, politics, and religion, and work, and the collection of things.<br/><br/> The&apos;ve been tol</span>
  <span id="freeText8408546090085746879" style="display:none">Quietly, gently, with dignity and respect, Boris Vian leads the astonished reader into an incongruent world, a surrealists dream where time and space have taken on more fluid dimensions. Manifestations, of painting and literature and poetry and stubborn dreams, stalk a Paris where the resistance to the Vichy regime is still going on. <br /><br />A la Breton, BV shines a brilliant light on the most revered of our illusions: love, politics, and religion, and work, and the collection of things.<br /><br /> The've been told that its good....In general it's found to be good . In fact nobody <br /> believes it. People do it out of habit and to avoid thinking about it. p82<br /><br /> In the background are the sounds of the city and the insistent throb of jazz.<br /> The beginning is at first bucolic, the humor off the walls until they begin to close in.<br /> <br /><br /> There is an index in the back which verifies each of the manifestations.</span>
