    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1361180979" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1361180979" />
    <a title="Gabrielle" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6753400-gabrielle"><img alt="Gabrielle" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1626286549p2/6753400.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1361180979?book_show_action=true">Aug 11, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Gabrielle" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Gabrielle" href="/user/show/6753400-gabrielle">Gabrielle</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Mass Market Paperback 9782010139345" href="/book/show/1519560.L_cume_des_jours">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6753400-gabrielle?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6753400-gabrielle?shelf=desert-island">desert-island</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6753400-gabrielle?shelf=reviewed">reviewed</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6753400-gabrielle?shelf=own-a-copy">own-a-copy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6753400-gabrielle?shelf=french">french</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6753400-gabrielle?shelf=je-suis-snob">je-suis-snob</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6753400-gabrielle?shelf=mandatory-reading">mandatory-reading</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6753400-gabrielle?shelf=used-bookstore-finds">used-bookstore-finds</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6753400-gabrielle?shelf=ouch-my-feels">ouch-my-feels</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6753400-gabrielle?shelf=stole-it-from-mom">stole-it-from-mom</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1361180979" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15400101684143940709">This is a book I have been re-reading periodically for the past fifteen years. I had my mother’s battered old copy for the longest time, it got misplaced in a move and I had to get a shiny new copy immediately. Boris Vian wrote a beautiful, sexy, tragic love story – and he did it with the most enchanting, surrealist prose one can imagine without ever becoming nauseatingly adorable.<br/><br/>The imaginary Paris the characters live in doesn’t know gravity, clouds talk, sunrays can be plucked like guitar str</span>
  <span id="freeText15400101684143940709" style="display:none">This is a book I have been re-reading periodically for the past fifteen years. I had my mother’s battered old copy for the longest time, it got misplaced in a move and I had to get a shiny new copy immediately. Boris Vian wrote a beautiful, sexy, tragic love story – and he did it with the most enchanting, surrealist prose one can imagine without ever becoming nauseatingly adorable.<br /><br />The imaginary Paris the characters live in doesn’t know gravity, clouds talk, sunrays can be plucked like guitar strings, philosophers are superstars and you can fish eel in your kitchen sink. But when people are ill, rooms shrink and windows will not let sunlight in. The characters are candid and a little vain: the world is their oyster and they will gorge themselves on refined food, elegant clothes, Jazz and fresh love. Colin loves Chloé and Chick loves Alise. It would be so easy if there wasn’t money to waste on books, an extravagant wedding or doctors… It would be so easy if these people did not have to work and could simply love each other all day…<br /><br />(Most romantic quote of all time, in my opinion: "Qu'est-ce que vous faites dans la vie, vous? - J'apprends des choses, dit Colin. Et j'aime Chloé.")<br /><br />Vian created a world of wonders to show us the incredible beauty of falling in love in sharp contrast with the gritty realities of loss and grief. The freshness and carelessness of youth faced with the unpleasant realities of adult life. The original title translates literally into “The foam (or froth) of days”, and that hints at the superficiality of the story: the beauty on the surface that shines brightly in the sunlight, hiding the murky, scary depths of the ocean. This only makes the read more heartbreaking because we all know the bitter taste of growing up, the fear of the unknown we have to face when we shed our teenage skin and realize the world is not the enchanted place we had in mind.<br /><br />The prose in stunning and rather complex. Vian uses word plays, metaphors, similes and other tricks of language to create magical images and concepts that are more dream than reality. It takes a bit of getting used to, but as soon as your brain gets used to it, you will get sucked into this bizarre poetry. It can’t be described and really must be experienced to be understood.<br /><br />This is a lush, erotic and blood-stained little book that I recommend to everyone. But be warned, it can crack your heart like an egg and you will find yourself feeling the sharp sting of that ending for a long time after you close the book. Also, I want a pianocktail.<br /><br />(I’ve only ever read this book in French, so I cannot recommend a good English translation, sadly. Also, I recently watched the movie adaptation, easily found under the title "Mood Indigo". I liked it, but it was just a little too twee for my taste. I also can't quite believe Romain Duris and Audrey Tautou as Colin and Chloé, mostly because the characters always felt to me like they were barely 20 years old, and those actors are now gently pushing 40. It was still a sweet little film, and fans of the book should like it.)</span>
  <a data-text-id="15400101684143940709" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


