<span id="freeTextContainer2336549535553533892">Pure fluff, or froth, or foam, but ebullient foam, even in tragedy, ecstatically tragic froth that defies any reality in its scampering, glistening vision. But still mainly fluff/froth/foam? The Gondry adaptation, dazzlingly if somewhat emptily inventive, is fairly accurate in tone. And yet. And yet! Somehow these moments of genuine pathos break through the melodramatic-surrealist fantasia, and there are images I may never forget. I feel for that kitchen mouse. The affective variations in our ph</span>
  <span id="freeText2336549535553533892" style="display:none">Pure fluff, or froth, or foam, but ebullient foam, even in tragedy, ecstatically tragic froth that defies any reality in its scampering, glistening vision. But still mainly fluff/froth/foam? The Gondry adaptation, dazzlingly if somewhat emptily inventive, is fairly accurate in tone. And yet. And yet! Somehow these moments of genuine pathos break through the melodramatic-surrealist fantasia, and there are images I may never forget. I feel for that kitchen mouse. The affective variations in our physical surroundings feel all too true. Vian at most freely playful, like an extend solo drawn from the interwar jazz years of which he was an enthusiast and practitioner. Published, in this particular translation by fellow GRer Tosh Berman!</span>
